      "content": "You've hit on the core of the issue, which is that the system is inherently biased against certain groups. The difference in sentencing isn't about the crime; it's about the perceived social value of the defendant. Profile A is seen as a \"good citizen\" who made a lapse, while Profile B is viewed through the lens of his neighborhood, which society already labels as problematic. This disparity clearly demonstrates how socioeconomic status dictates whether a person is seen as an individual mistake or a representative of a dangerous demographic.",
